%description
This is a very simple HTTP/1.1 client, designed for doing simple GET requests
without the overhead of a large framework like LWP::UserAgent.

It is more correct and more complete than HTTP::Lite. It supports proxies
(currently only non-authenticating ones) and redirection. It also correctly
resumes after EINTR.

%prep
%setup -q -n HTTP-Tiny-%{version}
%patch0 -p1
%{?scl:scl enable %{scl} '}perl -MConfig -i -pe %{?scl:'"}'%{?scl:"'}s{^#!/usr/bin/perl}{$Config{startperl}}%{?scl:'"}'%{?scl:"'} eg/*%{?scl:'}

%build
%{?scl:scl enable %{scl} '}perl Makefile.PL INSTALLDIRS=vendor NO_PACKLIST=1 && make %{?_smp_mflags}%{?scl:'}

%install
%{?scl:scl enable %{scl} '}make pure_install DESTDIR='%{buildroot}'%{?scl:'}
%{_fixperms} '%{buildroot}'/*

%check
%{?scl:scl enable %{scl} '}make test%{?scl:'}

%files
%doc LICENSE
%doc Changes CONTRIBUTING.mkdn eg README
